        <abstract> 
<p>Asks AdeC to observe two species of <hi rend="italic">Lythrum</hi> to see whether they are dimorphic as stated by Vaucher. CD can find no trace of this in dried specimens he has examined; "if either species present any difference in length of pistil and stamens, it is most likely that three forms should be presented".</p> 
        </abstract>
